de.boereck.matcher.helpers

Class DoubleMatchHelpers

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.boereck.matcher.helpers.DoubleMatchHelpers

  • public class DoubleMatchHelpers
extends Object
    This class provides static methods and fields that may help with defining consumers of cases in the found case library, helping defining matches for double values.
    This class is not intended to be instantiated or sub-classed.

    • Field Detail

      • filterNaN

        public static final DoubleFunction<OptionalDouble> filterNaN
        Reference to a function taking a double value and mapping it to an OptionalDouble. If the input to the function is NaN, then the function will return an empty optional, otherwise it will return an optional holding the input value.

      • filterInfinity

        public static final DoubleFunction<OptionalDouble> filterInfinity
        Reference to a function taking a double value and mapping it to an OptionalDouble. If the input to the function is positive or negative infinity, then the function will return an empty optional, otherwise it will return an optional holding the input value.

    • Method Detail

      • eq

        public static AdvDoublePredicate eq(double val,
                                    double eps)
        Returns a predicate checking if an input double value is equal to the given value val. Since calculations with double values have a limited precision, the check for equality should be done by checking if the two values are smaller than a given difference. In this case it is checked if the difference between val and an input value is smaller than eps.
        Parameters:
        val - value that input values will be compared with.
        eps - epsilon value by which the two compared values may differ and still be considered equal.
        Returns:
        function checking if an input double value is equal to value val (by checking if the difference is smaller than eps).
